US researchers claim that exact prices of goods on eBay attract higher offers than round numbers . 
  Sellers who end their price with ‘00’ typically receive offers that are five to eight per cent lower than those with more specific prices . 
  When the initial price is a round number, such as $1,000 , the average counteroffer is between 5 and 8 per cent higher than if it is a non-round number . 
  But sellers with round numbers are more likely to close a deal quickly . 
  Researchers from Cornell University and eBay Research Labs plotted how much goods sold for . 
  They found that items with precise prices attract higher counter offers . 
 